Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Most parameters are within normal limits. Notable findings include mildly low total CO₂, which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis or compensated respiratory alkalosis, and elevated hemoglobin and MCHC, possibly indicating mild dehydration or hemoconcentration. Urine specific gravity is low, which may reflect dilute urine or overhydration. No evidence of infection or renal dysfunction. Clinical correlation is recommended.
